<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>JSON REST API</title>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>JSON REST API</h1>
    <p>Select a route to explore:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>
            <strong>GET /</strong><br>
            <a href="http://localhost:8080/">
                http://localhost:8080/
            </a>
            <br>
            Home page
        </li>

        <br>

        <li>
            <strong>GET /user</strong><br>
            <a href="http://localhost:8080/user">
                http://localhost:8080/user
            </a>
            <br>
            Display all users
        </li>

        <br>

        <li>
            <strong>POST /user/:id/Edit</strong><br>
            Example:
            <code>http://localhost:8080/user/1/Edit</code>
            <br>
            Opens the edit form for a user.
        </li>

        <br>

        <li>
            <strong>PUT /user/:id</strong><br>
            Example:
            <code>http://localhost:8080/user/1</code>
            <br>
            Updates the selected user.
        </li>

        <br>

        <li>
            <strong>DELETE /user/:id</strong><br>
            Example:
            <code>http://localhost:8080/user/1</code>
            <br>
            Deletes the selected user.
        </li>
    </ul>

    <hr>

    <p>
        <strong>Note:</strong> Only <code>GET</code> routes can be opened directly
        in a browser. The <code>POST</code>, <code>PUT</code>, and
        <code>DELETE</code> routes are triggered through forms inside the
        application.
    </p>

</body>
</html>